      • continueWith

        Operations<T> continueWith(Proc0 func)
        Add a continueWith operation to the output from this publisher. The continueWith operation will pass through all the input elements and when the publisher is complete it will call the func function. It is the responsibility of the func function to call onComplete().
        Parameters:
        func - the function to call when all elements is processed.
        Returns:
        a new builder that wraps the output.

      • accumulate

        Operations<T> accumulate(T initial,
                         Func2<T,T,T> func)
        Add a accumulate operation to the output from this publisher. The accumulate operation call the func on each element sequentually with the the value of the previous calculation as the first parameter. After each calculation the result is emitted.
        Parameters:
        initial - an initial seed value. Can be null.
        func - the accumulate function.
        Returns:
        a new builder that wraps the output.
